The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26 : The home ministry has allowed citizens to fly the national flag even at night, provided the flagpole is tall and the flag well-illuminated.           
	The decision follows a proposal from industrialist Naveen Jindal, who had earlier won a court battle in the 1990s claiming that hoisting the Tricolour was a fundamental right.                   
	 Kota (PTI): The death toll in the collapse of an under-construction bridge over the Chambal river rose to 22 on Saturday with the recovery of three more bodies. Two officials arrested in connection with the accident were remanded in police custody for five days. Efforts are under way to locate missing labourers, said police.                   
	Srinagar: Five BSF jawans were injured on Saturday in an explosion blamed on militants who had crossed the Jammu border to disrupt fencing work. They (the jawans) have minor injuries, J.B. Sangwan, the BSFs DIG in Jammu, said.                  
	 Jaipur (PTI): An Indian working at Medina airport in Saudi Arabia managed to board an Air India flight, carrying 273 Haj pilgrims home, without a ticket and passport and travelled here after hiding in the planes toilet. Police said the presence of Uttar Pradesh native Habib came to light when a passenger went to the toilet.                                                                                                                                              
